The loop iterates `i` up to the last index, so `nums[i + 1]` attempts to access an index equal to `len(nums)`, which is out of bounds; change the range to `range(len(nums) - 1)`.

```python
def is_sorted_ascending(nums):
    for i in range(len(nums) - 1):
        if nums[i] > nums[i + 1]:
            return False
    return True
